The paper is primarily focused on implementing an analytical RDBMS in pure JavaScript, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of split-execution strategies, which involves distributing query operators between the browser and backend servers, and this could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of compiled query plans, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for in-browser interactive analytics, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
